  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures by presenting statistical failure patterns (counts per ASR and per TTS), using those patterns to compare relative ASR reliability, and performing a manual analysis that groups false positives into concrete cause categories (e.g., TTS errors, text-preprocessing limitations, ambiguous audio). However, it does not perform deeper diagnostic analysis that links failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., reliance on spurious features, dataset bias, or neuron/activation-level behavior) nor does it analyze model internals (the approach is explicitly black-box). Thus the paper provides partial diagnostic insight (statistical patterns and cause categories) but not explanations tied to internal model weaknesses.",
